Package treeexpressioncalculator

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Visitor
    An interface to facilitate performing a certain action each time an element in a data structure is visited
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BinaryTree
    A binary tree in which each node has two children.
    ExpressionTokenizer
    A class that breaks up a string describing an expression into tokens: numbers, parentheses, and operators.
    TreeEvaluator
    A class that evaluates an expression by arranging operands and values into a binary tree, performing a postorder traversal on the tree to put the elements into a queue in Reverse Polish Notation form, and then calculating the value of the entire expression by using a stack.
    TreeExpressionCalculator
    A program that calculates the value of an expression consisting of numbers, arithmetic operators, and parentheses.
